title: Frank Lloyd Wright Glasner House Clock
description:
Sleek lines and a minimalist clock face focus attention on the mineral glass panel that features a design adapted from a Frank Lloyd Wright® (American, 1867–1959) window in the W.A. Glasner House in Glencoe, IL.

6 1/4 x 6 1/4 x 2 in. Requires one AA battery (not included).
